-- HSBC names Haythorne, Che Ning as co-heads of AsiaPac banking
-- By Lawrence White
-- Wed Jun 04, 2014 12:04AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, June 4 (Reuters) - HSBC Holdings Plc <HSBA.L><0005.HK> named on Tuesday Martin Haythorne and Che Ning Liu as co-heads of banking for Asia Pacific, according to an internal memo seen by Reuters.

Haythorne and Che Ning will take over formally on Sept. 1 the role of Russell Julius, who is transferring to London. [ID:nL3N0OE25W] The two executives will report to Robin Phillips, global head of banking, and Gordon French, head of global banking and markets in Asia Pacific, the memo said. An HSBC spokesman in Hong Kong confirmed the moves.